{
  "stem": "5810.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I believe it was a first cousin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The name escapes me now.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a trial.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was-- that was quite an ordeal, which I might tell your story later.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That came after the war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that is why the Germans had our names.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But we contacted that person.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in those days the underground was quite active in placing Jews in orphanages, in convents, in gentile Belgian families that their purpose was to save Jews privately and so on.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were then given the name of a Belgian gentile family that would have-- that was willing to hide us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All three of us at the time, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we went there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a deal was struck because I'm afraid that not all Belgians were doing it to save Jews, or they cared about Jews, in fact, It's safe to say that the majority was just anti-Semitic and as bad to the Jews as-- as I found out later, that the Germans were.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So these people were quite willing to take us on for a fee.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And luckily enough, in those days, for whatever little that my father had put away, we had a little bit of money.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I understand also that the underground did subsidize somewhat the people with food and money for food, whoever was willing to hide Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I assume today that there was a combination of subsidizing from the underground, and the monies that we were able to give them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "However, that was a nightmare.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What were the names of this Belgian family?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jeanne and Andre-- I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jeanne and Emile Barniche.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They also had a son-- two sons actually-- one that was in the house while we were hiding.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His name was Ferdinand, who was my age by the way.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
